Timeline

Entry-level data engineer

Phase 1 - through 6 weeks
.SQL 
    .master joins, subqueries, window functions, and CTEs 
.Python
    .scripting, loops, data structures, and file handling for data manipulation 
.Linux & Git
    .basic command-line ops, bash scripting, and version control 
.Data modelling 
    .normalization, indexing, and Star vs Snowflake schemas 


Phase 3 - by week 12
.ETL processes 
    .extract, transform, and load data
    .use Python to move data from APIs/sources to storage 
.data warehousing
    .experience cloud-based data warehouses like Snowflake, BigQuery, or Redshift
.orchestration
    .schedule pipelines using Apache Airflow, Mage, or Prefect 


Phase 3  - by week 16
.cloud platforms 
    .either AWS/ Azure/ GCP 
    .learn their storage (S3/ Blob) and compute (Lambda/ Glue/ Databricks) services 
.big data tools 
    .distributed computing with Apache Spark


Phase 4  -  week 17+ 
.end-to-end project
    .build a project that scrapes data from an API, processes it with Spark/Python, loads it into a cloud warehouse, and schedules it with Airflow  
.dataOps 
    .implement basic data quality checks and containerize applications with Docker 